goals.question: What is the distribution of miles driven per year?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of miles driven per year and identify any outliers.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between the age of the car and the amount of gas used?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of year vs gas
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is a trend between the age of the car and the amount of gas used.

goals.question: What is the average gas consumption per mile?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of gas per mile

goals.question: What is the distribution of gas consumption?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of gas consumption and identify any outliers.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between the side of the car and the amount of gas used?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['miles'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Miles')
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven Per Year')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['year'], data['gas'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Gas')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between the age of the car and the amount of gas used?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['gas_per_mile'] = data['gas'] / data['miles']
    avg_gas_per_mile = data.groupby('year')['gas_per_mile'].mean()
    
    plt.bar(avg_gas_per_mile.index, avg_gas_per_mile.values)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Gas Consumption per Mile')
    plt.title('What is the average gas consumption per mile?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['gas'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Gas Consumption')
    plt.axvline(data['gas'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['gas'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Gas Consumption')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of gas consumption?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='gas', by='side', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('Is there a correlation between the side of the car and the amount of gas used?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Side')
    ax.set_ylabel('Gas')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend(title='Side', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
